<div id="review_1578130670" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1578130670" />
    <a title="Yousif Al Zeera" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12086858-yousif-al-zeera"><img alt="Yousif Al Zeera" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1577973191p2/12086858.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1578130670?book_show_action=true">Mar 13, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Yousif Al Zeera" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Yousif Al Zeera" href="/user/show/12086858-yousif-al-zeera">Yousif Al Zeera</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12086858-yousif-al-zeera?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12086858-yousif-al-zeera?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1578130670" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9551319160087115838">Levitt and Dubner continue to dazzle readers, freaks and soon-to-be-freaks with their fascinating way of combining data and narration to present interesting (and very much informative) stories on various fields.<br/><br/>In this book, the &quot;theoretical&quot; ratio slightly increased than the previous two books as the intention is lay down the foundations of &quot;how to think like a freak&quot;, basically how to rely more on &quot;data&quot; and less on &quot;anecdote&quot;. It is still full of splendid stories.</span>
  <span id="freeText9551319160087115838" style="display:none">Levitt and Dubner continue to dazzle readers, freaks and soon-to-be-freaks with their fascinating way of combining data and narration to present interesting (and very much informative) stories on various fields.<br /><br />In this book, the "theoretical" ratio slightly increased than the previous two books as the intention is lay down the foundations of "how to think like a freak", basically how to rely more on "data" and less on "anecdote". It is still full of splendid stories.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9551319160087115838" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
