    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1820962973" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1820962973" />
    <a title="Nguyen Linh Chi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/60897821-nguyen-linh-chi"><img alt="Nguyen Linh Chi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1516452924p2/60897821.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1820962973?book_show_action=true">Nov 24, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nguyen Linh Chi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nguyen Linh Chi" href="/user/show/60897821-nguyen-linh-chi">Nguyen Linh Chi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1820962973" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4228919382654736408">One of the most overrated books. Don&apos;t understand why it is a best-seller on Amazon. The author has stated some intriguing thoughts, for example, the hardest words in the world are &quot;I don&apos;t know&quot; and preconceptions prevents people from seeing things the way they are. However, his arguments are based mostly on his personal ideas and anecdotes. Moreover, these arguments are presented disorderly, which make it hard for readers to follow.<br/><br/>Not recommend purchasing this book. I heard that his 2 books <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1202.Freakonomics_A_Rogue_Economist_Explores_the_Hidden_Side_of_Everything__Freakonomics___1_' title='Freakonomics A Rogue Economist Explores the Hidden Side of Everything (Freakonomics, #1) by Steven D. Levitt' rel='nofollow noopener'>F</a></span>
  <span id="freeText4228919382654736408" style="display:none">One of the most overrated books. Don't understand why it is a best-seller on Amazon. The author has stated some intriguing thoughts, for example, the hardest words in the world are "I don't know" and preconceptions prevents people from seeing things the way they are. However, his arguments are based mostly on his personal ideas and anecdotes. Moreover, these arguments are presented disorderly, which make it hard for readers to follow.<br /><br />Not recommend purchasing this book. I heard that his 2 books <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1202.Freakonomics_A_Rogue_Economist_Explores_the_Hidden_Side_of_Everything__Freakonomics___1_" title="Freakonomics A Rogue Economist Explores the Hidden Side of Everything (Freakonomics, #1) by Steven D. Levitt" rel="nofollow noopener">Freakonomics: A Rogue Economist Explores the Hidden Side of Everything</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25245393.Super_Freakonomics" title="Super Freakonomics by Steven D. Levitt" rel="nofollow noopener">Super Freakonomics</a> are extraordinary. Should I be brave to try these books after bad experience with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17349190.Think_like_a_Freak_The_Authors_of_Freakonomics_Offer_to_Retrain_Your_Brain" title="Think like a Freak The Authors of Freakonomics Offer to Retrain Your Brain by Steven D. Levitt" rel="nofollow noopener">Think like a Freak: The Authors of Freakonomics Offer to Retrain Your Brain</a>?</span>
  <a data-text-id="4228919382654736408" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


